 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Segmentation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pylab as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "from wildboar import annotate\n",
    "from wildboar.utils.plot import plot_time_domain"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First, we download a dataset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x = np.loadtxt(\"https://drive.google.com/uc?export=download&id=1DYG3rwW_zpd-7lcgYeL0Y2nHtkr2Fi0O\")\n",
    "x = x[20000:30000]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next, we find the change points that segment the time series."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "segments = annotate.segment(x=x, n_segments=3, window=200)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finally, we plot the change points that segment the time series."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 864x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 4), sharex=True)\n",
    "plot_time_domain(x, ax=ax)\n",
    "\n",
    "for segment in segments:\n",
    "    ax.axvspan(segment, segment + 1, 0, 1, color=\"gray\", alpha=0.9, linestyle=\"dashed\")"
   ]
  }
 ],
